                                   Max-chunks

  From Soar Wiki

   This is part of the Soar Command Line Interface.

                                      Name

   max-chunks - Limit the number of chunks created during a decision cycle.

   Priority: 3 ; Status: Complete

                                    Synopsis

 max-chunks [n]

                                    Options

   +-----------------------------------------------------------+
   |n|Maximum number of chunks allowed during a decision cycle.|
   +-----------------------------------------------------------+

                                  Description

   The max-chunks command is used to limit the maximum number of chunks that
   may be created during a decision cycle. The initial value of this variable
   is 50; allowable settings are any integer greater than 0.

                               Structured Output

On Query

 <result>
   <arg name="value" type="int">max_chunks</arg>
 </result>

Otherwise

 <result output="raw">true</result>

                                  Error Values

During Parsing

   kTooManyArgs, kIntegerMustBePositive

During Execution

   kAgentRequired
